From: Fan Wu <wufan@kernel.org>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 19:55:13 -0700
Subject: [RFC PATCH 0/4] IPE support for authorizing a trusted composefs image

This series lets IPE authorize files that come from a specific, trusted
composefs image, identified by the fs-verity digest of its backing EROFS
metadata file.

A composefs is an overlayfs over a file-backed EROFS metadata image. That
image records each file's data-blob fs-verity digest, but the blobs live in
a separate store, so the image's own fs-verity digest binds a file's
content only when overlayfs checks each blob against its recorded digest,
which it does only under the overlayfs verity=require option.

d_real(dentry, D_REAL_METADATA) already walks the (possibly nested) overlay
stack to that EROFS metadata dentry, but it cannot tell the caller whether
the composefs enforces verity=require. So patch 1 adds a helper that does
the same walk and hands back the dentry only for a verity=require
composefs. This duplicates d_real() and adds a new public overlayfs
interface; I found no cleaner way, and better ideas are welcome.

The rest follows: at mount time erofs publishes the backing file's
fs-verity digest on the EROFS metadata root inode via
security_inode_setintegrity(); IPE takes the dentry from patch 1, reads the
digest off that root inode's security blob, and matches it against the
policy.

Fan Wu (4):
  ovl: add helper to resolve a file's composefs metadata dentry
  lsm: add LSM_INT_BACKING_FILE_FSVERITY_DIGEST integrity type
  erofs: expose backing-file fs-verity digest to LSMs on file-backed
    mount
  ipe: add support for composefs as a trust provider

